<div id="bookLandingPage" class="container-fluid">
    <div class="jumbotron page-section book-page-section">
      <div class="book-cover"><img src="<%= asset_path('books/book.jpg') %>" /></div>
      <h1 class="title">The Zone of Interest</h1>
      <h2> Martin Amis</h2>
      <div id="launchCountdown"></div>
    </div>
  <div class="jumbotron page-section abstract-page-section">
    <h2>About the book</h2><br/>
    <p>The Zone of Interest isn't Martin Amis's first attempt to write about the Holocaust -- Time’s Arrow told the story of a doctor working during the time period. His newest novel approaches the topic head-on, setting a love story in the unlikely setting of a concentration camp.</p>
    <h3><b>Publish Date:</b> July 21, 2015</h3>
  </div>
  <div class="jumbotron page-section email-page-section">
    <h2>Notify me when the book is available</h2><br/>
    <form role="form">
      <div class="form-group">
        <label for="name">Name</label>
        <input type="text" class="form-control" id="name" placeholder="Enter Name">
      </div>
      <div class="form-group">
        <label for="email">Email address</label>
        <input type="email" class="form-control" id="email" placeholder="Enter Email">
      </div>
      <button type="submit" class="btn btn-primary">Keep me posted</button>
    </form>
  </div>
  <div class="jumbotron page-section author-page-section">
    <h2>About the author</h2><br/>
    <div class="author-pic"></div>
    <h3>Martin Amis</h3>
    <p>Martin Louis Amis is an English novelist. His best-known novels are Money (1984) and London Fields (1989). He has received the James Tait Black Memorial Prize for his memoir Experience and has been listed for the Booker Prize twice to date (shortlisted in 1991 for Time's Arrow and longlisted in 2003 for Yellow Dog)</p>
  </div>
</div>


